HEADWORD: Esemplastic
<hw>Es`em*plas"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'es</grk> into, to + <grk>"en</grk> one + <grk>plastiko`s</grk>
molded, formed. See <er>Plastic</er>.]</ety> <def>Shaped into one;
tending to, or formative into, unity.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Coleridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
